## Popup-Related Renames (Select, Cascader, TreeSelect, DatePicker, TimePicker, AutoComplete, Mentions)

- `dropdownClassName` / `popupClassName` → `classNames.popup.root`
- `dropdownStyle` → `styles.popup.root`
- `dropdownRender` → `popupRender`
- `onDropdownVisibleChange` → `onOpenChange`
- `bordered` → `variant`

## Data-Driven Pattern (use `items`, not children)

```tsx
// BAD — deprecated children pattern
<Menu><Menu.Item key="1">Home</Menu.Item></Menu>
<Select><Select.Option value="a">A</Select.Option></Select>

// GOOD — data-driven items/options
<Menu items={[{ key: '1', label: 'Home' }]} />
<Select options={[{ value: 'a', label: 'A' }]} />
```

Applies to: Menu, Tabs, Steps, Breadcrumb, Collapse, Timeline, Select, Mentions.

## General Rules

- Always use `open` (not `visible`) for Modal, Drawer, Dropdown, Tooltip, Popover, Popconfirm.
- Use CSS-in-JS tokens via `ConfigProvider theme` — no Less variables or style imports.
- Import icons from `@ant-design/icons` (tree-shakeable, v6 compatible).
- Use `App.useApp()` for `message`, `notification`, and `modal` — avoid static methods.
